nd trust me, when you play the Caro-Kann as Black, you don't want to face this position on move 10!} Be4 11. Bxe6+ Kh7 12. g5 hxg5 (12... Qe7 13. Bf7 $1 hxg5 14. Qd2 $3) 13. Nf7 *

