antee you, you can get a winning position against 2600+ FIDE GMs with it coz everyone misses White's main idea of this move. They think White's idea is to go Bxe6 !! and then Qg6 . They see that Nbd7 counters this move and immediately play it. But that is not the point of} 10. Qd3 $1 {The whole idea is the f5 -square!!!! O-O? is too slow and does nothing to stop Black's main counterplay with} Nbd7 $1 {Black has almost no problems. That is why it is imperative to stop ... Nbd7 .} 11. Nxf7 $2 Kxf7 12. Qe2 Nd5 13. Qf3+ N7f6 {and Black is a piece up with no problems.}) 10... b5 { A popular move. Black missed what White's last move was threatening.} 11. Bxe6 {Brilliant! Sacrificing the bishop to deflect the bishop from protecting the g6 -square.} Bxe6 (11... Qa5+ {was played in the game, but after} 12. b4 $1 { , White is +4 and completely winning:} Qxb4+ 13. c3 {.}) 12. Qg6+ Bf7 13. Qxf7# *

