pieces', but here it's a mistake, as the light squares are left weak.} 11. Qxf3 e6 $4 (11... Qxd4 $1 12. Qg3 g5 (12... Qg4 $1 13. Qc7 Nbd7 14. Bd2 {with chaos on the board. I would, of course, take White here, as Black's king on g7 is very weak.}) 13. Bxg5 $3 {Don't Boo – SPAM THE BRILLIANT EMOTE‼ The idea is to expose the black king to checks.} hxg5 14. Qxg5+ Kf7 15. Qg6#) 12. Qg3 Nbd7 $2 13. Qxg6# {CM Witty_Alien (2605) vs. BrainThinker22 (2603) Jan 30, 2024.}) 10... Bxf3 11. Qxf3 Qxd4 12. Qg3 ({ And now there is no ... Qg4 , which is what might have happened in the game with} 12. Re1 $6) 12... g5 13. Bxg5 {Brilliant!! Sacrificing the bishop to expose the black king.} hxg5 14. Qxg5+ Kf7 15. Bg6+ Kg7 16. Bf5+ Kf7 17. Qg6# { A beautiful display of how White uses the weak light squares.} *

