 {had to be played, attacking the rookie and the strong bishop on d3 .} 15. Rg4 Nxd3 16. Qxd3 Ne7 {with chances for both sides. Black is still a piece up but with a very weak king:} 17. Rf4+ Ke8 18. Qf3 {.}) 15. Qh5+ Kg8 16. Bxh6 {Sacrificing the bishop to open the g-file.} Qe7 ({ If Black takes the sacrificed bishop} 16... gxh6 {, they get mated on the light squares:} 17. Qg6+ Kh8 18. Qh7# {.}) 17. Bh7+ {Stop This Guy From Brillianting‼ Sacrificing the bishop to deflect the king on the h-file.} Kxh7 18. Bxg7+ ({3 Consecutive Brilliant Moves‼ Kxg7} 18. Rg4 Qg5 19. Rxg5 {1-0.}) *

