or Black. The game Witty_Alien (2343) vs. FM Apollonzerotv (2648), Dec 24, 2023 continued:} 12. dxe5 Nd5 13. Qg4 ({A fantastic move.} 13. Qh5 $2 {would be a mistake because of} Qe8 $1 14. Bg6 Qe7 {.}) 13... Qe7 14. Bxh6 Rf5 {An interesting move. Black is already a piece up, so they sacrifice the exchange to get two minor pieces for the rookie.} (14... Nd7 15. Bg5 $1 {Behold! It is important to play for attack and not for material.} (15. Qg6 $6 {This move is very human but not good, as Black's next move is very strong.} Rf5 $1 16. Bxf5 exf5 17. e6 Nf8 18. Qxg7+ $1 { Sacrificing a piece so the e-pawn can run.} Qxg7 19. Bxg7 Kxg7 20. e7 Bd7 21. exf8=Q+ Kxf8 22. f3 {. White has a much better endgame, but the game is far from over.}) 15... Qf7 16. Qh4 g6 17. c4 $1 Nb4 18. Bb1 $1 {It is very important for the bishop to stay on the b1 - h7 diagonal.} Nc5 19. Re3 { , in the Alien Gambit, the rookie on e1 almost always swings on e3 or e4 to join the attack on the kingside.} Bd7 20. Rh3 Qg7 21. Bxg6 $3 {and White is mating.}) 15. c4 {A very strong move! It is imperative to kick the pony on d5 before taking on f5 .} ({The game between CM Witty_Alien (2479) vs. BadTheory1 (2516), Dec 4, 2024, continued:} 15. Bxf5 $2 {The reason this move is bad is because the pony on d5 is too strong. I have noticed that after the white queen is on g4 and bishop on h6 , when you have the chance to kick the pony on d5 with c4 , do it ASAP!} exf5 16. Qg3 f4 $4 {( Be6⩲ )} 17. Qg6 $2 f3 $2 {(} 18. Qf7+ $1 {) e6} Kh8 19. c4 gxh6 20. cxd5 {Qg7 Qxg7+ Kxg7 d6 Kf6 e7} Bd7 { e8N+ Bxe8 Rxe8 Kf7 Rae1 a5 d7 1-0.}) 15... Nb4 16. Bxf5 exf5 17. Qg6 Bd7 (17... Be6 {was seen in CM Witty_Alien (2382) vs. GM MrTattaglia (2983) , Feb 15, 2025, which continued} 18. Bxg7 $3 {Brilliant!! Sacrificing the bishop to deflect the protection of the e6 -bishop.} Qf7 19. Qh6 Qxg7 20. Qxe6+ Qf7 21. Qc8+ Kg7 22. e6 {, the moment the pawn steps on e6 , all hope is lost for Black. They are getting mated.} Qe7 23. Re3 {, the rookie swing is very powerful.} f4 24. Rh3 Kf6 25. Qh8+ Kf5 26. Re1 $1 {and here Black resigned, as Rh5 is coming with mate to follow. What a pixel-perfect Alien Gambit game by White. They made no mistake, and 2600 FIDE-rated GM lost easily. If you know what you are doing as White, the win is inevitable. Feel free to see the game reaction on YouTube – Alien Gambit vs. (2983) GM .}) 18. Rad1 Be8 19. Rd8 { Brilliant!! Sacrificing the rookie to deflect the queen on protecting the g7 -pawn.} Qxd8 20. Qxg7# *

