or Black. The game Witty_Alien (2343) vs. FM Apollonzerotv (2648), Dec 24, 2023 continued:} 12. dxe5 Nd5 13. Qg4 ({A fantastic move.} 13. Qh5 $2 {would be a mistake because of} Qe8 $1 14. Bg6 Qe7 {.}) 13... Qe7 14. Bxh6 Qf7 (14... Nd7 15. Bg5 $1 {Behold! It is important to play for attack and not for material.} (15. Qg6 $6 {This move is very human but not good, as Black's next move is very strong.} Rf5 $1 16. Bxf5 exf5 17. e6 Nf8 18. Qxg7+ $1 {Sacrificing a piece so the e-pawn can run.} Qxg7 19. Bxg7 Kxg7 20. e7 Bd7 21. exf8=Q+ Kxf8 22. f3 {. White has a much better endgame, but the game is far from over.}) 15... Qf7 16. Qh4 g6 17. c4 $1 Nb4 18. Bb1 $1 {It is very important for the bishop to stay on the b1 - h7 diagonal.} Nc5 19. Re3 {, in the Alien Gambit, the rookie on e1 almost always swings on e3 or e4 to join the attack on the kingside.} Bd7 20. Rh3 Qg7 21. Bxg6 $3 {and White is mating.}) 15. Bg6 {Sacrificing a pawn with a check! But tactics come in a position of strength and Black is very undeveloped.} Qxf2+ 16. Kh1 gxh6 17. Bd3+ {The only move to win the game, but good enough. It's imperative to control the f1 -square, as we will see why.} (17. Be4+ $2 Kh8 18. Qg6 Qf7 19. Qxh6+ Kg8 20. Rf1 $2 Qxf1+ $3 {Daddy Issues, aka Back-Rank issues. With the bishop on d3 , this move would have not been possible.} 21. Rxf1 Rxf1# {.}) 17... Kh8 18. Qg6 Qf7 19. Qxh6+ Kg8 20. Rf1 Qg7 21. Bh7+ {Stop it bebeeee. Sacrificing the bishop to clear the attack on the f8 -rookie for the queen.} Kh8 (21... Qxh7 22. Rxf8#) 22. Rxf8+ Qxf8 23. Qxf8+ Kxh7 {White is mating with Rf1 .} 24. Rf1 {I have won so many games like this without thinking, as I know this line by heart. If you want, memorize the line; you will get it quite often, I assure you. Feel free to watch this funny reaction on YouTube – I think he said ALIEN GAMBIT .} *

