s imperative for Black to leave the pony on e5 and not give the critical h5 -square for the queen.} 12. Qf3 {Super duper strong move! It's time to transfer the queen to the kingside. This move also threatens Bxh6 !! Remember this move. If your pony still resides on e5 , then you transfer the queen to the kingside.} Rf8 13. Qg3 {Remember this queen transfer, my dear alien. If Black doesn't take on e5 , then you transfer the queen with Qf3 - g3 .} Nh5 14. Qg6 Ndf6 15. g4 {White is winning, as they get back their material with a winning game. I have gotten such wins very, very often, actually.} *

