E MOST COMMON MOVE HERE!! Black just doesn't like the pony, so they just take it. Also, they are up material, so on paper exchanges favor Black. And in Black's mind, in the last couple of moves, they did everything to make an artificial castle, so now they can safely exchange pieces.} 12. dxe5 Nd5 13. Qh5+ {White is winning. I have won like this a thousand times against CM, FM, IM, and GMs.} Kg8 14. Bxh6 {BRILLIANT!! White sacrifices the bishop to expose the black king to checks. This is the ultimate Alien Gambit attack. Queen, bishops, and rookies are coming over.} Nf8 ({➢} 14... gxh6 15. Qg6+ Kh8 (15... Kf8 16. Qxh6+ Kf7 {( Kg8} 17. Bh7 {Kf7 Qg6+ Kf8 Qg8+} Ke7 18. Qg7# {) Bg6+ and the bishop joins the mating net. That's All She Wrote. Kg8 ( Ke7 Qg7# ) Qh7+ Kf8 Qf7# .}) 16. Qh7# {.}) ({➢ The game between CM Witty_Alien (2534) vs. WGM DivyaDeshmukh23 (2627), Dec 6 2024, continued:} 14... Qe7 15. Bxg7 $3 {Destroying the king's shelter. ( Bh7+!! is another amazing move.)} Qxg7 (15... Kxg7 16. Re4 $1 {and Black cannot defend their king.}) 16. Qxe8+ Nf8 17. Re4 {, the rookie joins the attack, and there are no chances for Black. Please notice how the queenside pieces don't do anything for Black.} Ne7 18. Qh5 Nfg6 19. Rg4 Kf7 20. Re1 $1 {The last piece joins the attack.} Nf5 21. Bxf5 exf5 22. e6+ Bxe6 23. Rxe6 $3 {Removing one of the king's main defenders.} fxg4 24. Qf5+ Kg8 25. Rxg6 {GG, White is winning the queen and the game. If you want to see my reaction while playing my gambit against the Olympic champion, feel free to check the YouTube video – Alien Gambit vs. Divya Deshmukh .}) 15. Bxg7 {Don't Boo – SPAM THE BRILLIANT EMOTE‼️} Kxg7 16. Re4 {The key move! Now there is no defense against Rg4 +. } Ng6 ({Witty_Alien (2417) vs. IM Polina Shuvalova (2668) Jan 13, 2024, continued:} 16... Nf6 17. exf6+ Qxf6 18. Rg4+ Ng6 19. Rxg6+ {1-0.}) 17. Rg4 Nde7 18. Rxg6+ {Black's king defense is shattered.} Nxg6 19. Qxg6+ Kf8 20. Qh6+ Kg8 21. Bh7+ {Enjoy the beauty of exploring Back's weak light squares – a common theme in the Alien Gambit.} Kf7 22. Qg6+ Kf8 23. Qg8+ Ke7 24. Qg7# { Witty_Alien (2358) vs. GM gmjoey1 (2668) Dec 10, 2023, Blitz game. This was my BEST Alien Gambit win, and mainly thanks to this win, as it became viral on socials, the Alien Gambit became a book move. Feel free to check this short video here: https://www.youtube.com/shorts/u4VxYDouMDY And here we reached our end, my brothers and sisters. To summarize, we learned that the Alien Gambit is an OP Gambit. Why? Here's why. 1. It's very easy for White to play, as plans are similar regardless of Black's response. 2. Black always has problems with their king. 3. The most HUMAN way to defend against the Alien Gambit is a blunder for Black, as we saw in this game. 4. Black underestimates the gambit, as they see the slow approach you are taking with Bd3 , O-O , and Re1 . Only to find themselves in a losing position very fast with brilliants. 5. Caro-Kann players are usually solid players. That is why it's so difficult for them to defend, as the position becomes super duper tactical in no time. This is the time to make your knowledge of romantic chess shine. I believe you will be very proud of your games. 6. The Alien Gambit is for Bullet, Blitz, and maybe even Rapid. Your opponent has no time to figure out everything, while you know tips/tricks/brilliants and plans. It's a free win‼️ 7. It's very easy to get the Alien Gambit, as Caro-Kann is one of the most popular openings in the world. In our Discord Server,  https://discord.com/invite/ Cc5yVwjPxz, with 3700+ members, you can share your Alien Gambit games with the community and ping me if you have any questions. I always reply when I see the message. Good luck, have fun, Godspeed.} *

