e played ... Kg8 .} 10. dxe5 Nd5 ({After} 10... Ng4 11. Bg6+ $3 Kxg6 12. Qxd8 {, White is winning, as they are a queen up.}) 11. c4 $1 {Kicking the pony to clear the d-file for a nasty trick.} Nb6 12. Bg6+ $3 {Don't Boo – SPAM THE BRILLIANT EMOTE‼️} Kxg6 13. Qxd8 {with a winning game, as White is a queen up.}) 8... Bf5 9. g4 Nxg4 10. Nh4 {Full piece down, but thank God chess is a practical game. Here, it is very easy to play for White; Black has to be very careful. The idea is to use Black's weak king and uncoordinated pieces.} g6 11. Nxf5 gxf5 12. Qf3 Qd7 {A good move, if only White's next move didn't exit.} (12... Nf6 $1 { Sacrificing the f5 -pawn to protect their pieces and attack the d5 -pawn.} 13. b3 $1 {is a very nice move. Now, ... Qxd5 will be met with Bc4 winning the queen.} (13. Qxf5 $2 Qxd5 {and Black is winning, as White is forced to exchange queens.}) 13... Nxd5 $4 {is a blunder, as now White will dominate on the light squares.} ({After} 13... Qd6 14. Bb2 Rg8 {, Black is much better as they are a piece up, but their king is weak, and White's king is safer after O-O-O .}) 14. Qxf5+ Ke8 {( Nf6} 15. Bc4 {Ke8 Bb2!} Bg7 16. Qg6+ Kf8 17. Qf7+ { ) Qh5+ Kd7 Qxd5++– and White got their piece back with an easy win, as Black's king is super duper exposed.}) 13. Bb5 {Is chess not beautiful? Is chess not romantic? Is chess not aesthetic? Sacrificing the bishop to deflect the protection of the f5 -pawn.} Qxb5 (13... Qd6 $6 14. Qxf5+ Nf6 15. Bc4 Nbd7 16. Bf4 Qb6 17. O-O-O {and White is completely winning. We have the e- and g-files for the rooks, and with the light squares weaknesses, there is no hope for Black.}) 14. Qxf5+ Nf6 15. Qe6+ Ke8 16. Qc8+ Kf7 17. Qe6+ Ke8 (17... Kg7 $4 18. Rg1+ Kh7 19. Qf5#) 18. Qc8+ {With a romantic draw. Yes, draws can be romantic. :)))} *

