e played ... Kg8 .} 10. dxe5 Nd5 ({After} 10... Ng4 11. Bg6+ $3 Kxg6 12. Qxd8 {, White is winning, as they are a queen up.}) 11. c4 $1 {Kicking the pony to clear the d-file for a nasty trick.} Nb6 12. Bg6+ $3 {Don't Boo – SPAM THE BRILLIANT EMOTE‼️} Kxg6 13. Qxd8 {with a winning game, as White is a queen up.}) 8... Qd6 { A very strong move, blocking the pawn, threatening ... Nxd5 and ... e6 . But do not lose heart. Only people who have looked at it with an engine play it. When you rematch this player, time to switch to Ne5+!} 9. c4 e6 10. Be2 exd5 11. cxd5 {CM Witty_Alien (2600) vs. CM Schachkatze2000 (2703) Oct 4, 2024 continued:} Bf5 ({After} 11... Qxd5 $4 12. Bc4 $3 Qxc4 13. Ne5+ {, White wins the queen and the game.}) 12. O-O Nbd7 13. b3 g5 14. Ba3 b6 15. Nd4 Be4 16. Bb5 {Black is better, but the position is chaotic, and that is what we hope for when we play the Alien Gambit, but trust me, not what Black is hoping when playing the Caro-Kann. :D} *

