ey are a queen up.}) 11. c4 $1 {Kicking the pony to clear the d-file for a nasty trick.} Nb6 12. Bg6+ $3 { Don't Boo – SPAM THE BRILLIANT EMOTE‼️} Kxg6 13. Qxd8 {with a winning game, as White is a queen up.}) 8... Kg8 9. Bc4+ e6 (9... Kh7 $4 {blunders mate:} 10. Qd3+ g6 11. Qxg6# {.}) 10. O-O ({A very, very difficult to move to make, but imperative to be done. You have to sac the d4 -pawn for lead in development. Holding on the pawn is too slow.} 10. c3 $6 Nc6 11. Ng6 cxd4 12. cxd4 Bb4+ 13. Bd2 Qxd4 {with a win for Black, as everything is hanging for White.}) 10... cxd4 {Too greedy. Black has to develop their queenside ASAP.} 11. Ng6 Nc6 {A very nice move. They know that the rookie on h8 is not as important as the strong pony on g6 . If White takes the rookie, then Black will have two minor pieces and an amazing center.} 12. Re1 {Super duper important moment here. It's IMPERATIVE to understand that we take the rookie on h8 as a LAST resort, as the pony is almost always stronger than the rookie on h8 . In the words of Hikaru: 'And that, my friends, is why the Alien Gambit is a good opening; you end up with a dead rook on the corner very quickly, and it is very, very hard to play.' Black's king is bugged on g8 and the rookie is super duper passive and helps Black's king get mated.} Bd6 13. Rxe6 {So romantic. The rook is sacrificed to have mindblowing play on the light squares. } Bxe6 {Black has to take.} 14. Bxe6+ Kh7 15. Qd3 {They key move. Black is getting mated, as the double check is too deadly.} Re8 16. Nf8+ Kh8 17. Qh7+ { DID SHE CALL HIM BEBE! The queen is sacrificed for Smothered Mate.} Nxh7 18. Ng6# {CM Witty_Alien (2603) vs. CM queensandpawns (2560), Jun 20, 2024.} *

