 , so sacrificing a pawn to decoy the bishop and then ... Nd4 comes with tempo, attaching the bishop on b5 .} 19. Bxb5 Nd4 20. Bd3 Nxf5 21. Nxh8 Kxh8 22. Rxf5 ({Brilliant!! This move would not have been possible if} 22. Rfe1 {hadn't been played. The whole difference!}) 22... exf5 23. Re8+ Kh7 24. Rxc8 {So romantic. Sacrificing the rookie to decoy the rookie on c8 so that Bxf5 + will be devastating.} Rxc8 25. Bxf5+ g6 26. Bxc8 *

