h the pony rather than the pawn.} 10. Bd3 { Such backward moves are so difficult to make, and to be honest, I always miss them. That is why you are learning this course, so you don't have to miss them. The idea is to play on the light squares and their only defender is the bishop on f5 .} Qc8 {The best and only way to protect the bishop that does not lose the game. Have fun finding this move in bullet or blitz. Alien Gambit so OP!!!} (10... e6 $4 11. Bxf5 exf5 12. Qh5+ Ke7 13. Qf7+ Kd6 14. Nc4# {, and if g6?? Bxf5 gxf5 Qh5# .}) 11. Qh5+ g6 12. Nxg6 Bg4 {A difficult move to see, but it keeps the chaos on the board.} 13. Qh4 Rg8 14. h3 Bf5 15. Qh5 Bxg6 16. Bxg6+ Kd8 17. Bf7 {White is better thanks to the active pieces and safer king, but Black is still a piece up. The pawn on g2 is immune, as Bxd5 would win the game.} *

