)) Kxb6 ( Kb7 Qxc6+ Kb8 Qc7+ Ka8 b7# , beautiful pawn checkmate. :)) Qxc6# ) Qc4# .}) 29. Qd7#) 28... Qg2+ 29. Kc3 Nxe5 30. dxe5 Rh8 31. e6+ Kb6 32. Be3+ Ka6 33. b4 b5 34. a4 bxc4 35. b5+ Kb7 36. Qf7+ Ka8 37. Qxa7# {, checkmate!! No, you are not dreaming. Hikaru, with all due respect, just got destroyed with the Alien Gambit!! Well played, MidnightHorizon! If Hikaru, the one and only, can lose to the Alien Gambit already on move 11, imagine us mortals. This game, once again, proves that the Alien Gambit works in all levels. ❤}) 20... Nd7 21. Nf7 {White is completely winning, as the d6 -bishop is hanging, with an exchange and two pawns up.} *

