 Black any chance of coming back.}) 18... Qb6 (18... Bc5 19. Nc4+ Kd5 20. b3 {with mate to follow – Rd1 is threatened.}) 19. Rd1 Nbd7 (19... Qa6+ {or Qb5+ is just a check and after} 20. Kf2 {, mate is still inevitable given the checks on c7 and f4 .}) 20. Nc4# {Another beautiful central checkmate.} *

