erative to gain access to the b1 - h7 diagonal, so this weird-looking move makes sense. :)))) This move works because there is no ... Nb4 ! since the pony on d5 is pinned.} b5 12. Bxd5+ cxd5 13. Kxc2 {White is winning. Black's light squares are soooooos weak. Did I mention how weak they are? I think I forgot. :)))} *

