ition on move 10!} b5 {The most popular move, gaining space on the queenside while attacking the bishop on c4 .} 11. Bb3 c5 (11... c5 $3 {is a very brilliant and strong move, discovered by a dear friend of mine and Twitch, Discord, and club mod Fatma Satılmış. The idea is to trap White's bishop on b3 . Do not be afraid of this move. Only people with engine analysis play it, and White is still doing well. Don't spend much time studying this move, as I have never faced it. Everyone plays ... Be4 . Only in our arenas, this move is played. It's very difficult to see.}) 12. gxf5 c4 13. fxe6 cxb3 14. axb3 Nc6 {Using tactics to exchange pieces, which favors Black, as they are a piece up.} 15. O-O (15. Nxc6 Qd5 16. O-O Qxc6 17. Qe2 { with chaos on the board. I prefer White due to the weak black king, strong a-file, and e6 -pawn.}) 15... Nxe5 16. dxe5 Qxd1 17. Rxd1 Nh5 {Equal game but chaos, aka we win. :)))} *

