have no developed pieces. Beautiful, isn't it?} Bxd1 17. Rxd1 Rd8 18. Rxd8+ Kxd8 19. Qd2+ Ke8 (19... Kc7 20. Be5+ Kb6 {( Kc8} 21. Bxe6 {) Qb4# .}) 20. Bxe6 ({Since the queen is not on g6 , this move is possible. Mate will follow: Nf6} 20. Bf6 exf6 21. Qd7+ {.}) *

