t's important to put the bishop on a5 if the queen is on g6 and put the bishop on c3 if the queen is on h7 .} ({It's important to stop 17...Rd8 ! as we can't take on e6 in the variation when the queen is on h7 :} 16. Bc3 $4 Bxd1 17. Rxd1 Rd8 $1 18. Rxd8+ Kxd8 19. Qd2+ Ke8 20. Bxe6 Qxe6 {. That is why when the queen is on g6 , the bishop is put on a5 to stop ... Rd8 !}) 16... Bxd1 17. Rxd1 b6 18. Bxe6 {Sacrificing the bishop to take on e6 and attack on c6 , which cannot be defended.} Rd8 {This is the most human move to play as exchanges favor Black as they are billions of pieces up, but in this case, the queenside is left unprotected.} 19. Rxd8+ Kxd8 20. Qd2+ Kc7 21. Qd7+ Kb8 22. Qc8# *

