7 18. Qd3 {, and as you can see, White's pieces are fully active, while Black's pieces look super-duper uncoordinated.} Nd5 19. Qxh7 {, bye-bye rookie. White is winning.}) 16... hxg5 17. Rad1 Qxd1 18. Rxd1+ Kc7 19. g4 {Making luft.} Rd8 20. Rxd8 Kxd8 21. Qxg5 {White is a queen up, but Black has enough pieces for it, though they are so uncoordinated.} *

