antee you, you can get a winning position against 2600+ FIDE GMs with it coz everyone misses White's main idea of this move. They think White's idea is to go Bxe6 !! and then Qg6 . They see that Nbd7 counters this move and immediately play it. But that is not the point of} 10. Qd3 $1 {The whole idea is the f5 -square!!!! O-O? is too slow and does nothing to stop Black's main counterplay with} Nbd7 $1 {Black has almost no problems. That is why it is imperative to stop ... Nbd7 .} 11. Nxf7 $2 Kxf7 12. Qe2 Nd5 13. Qf3+ N7f6 {and Black is a piece up with no problems.}) 10... Nd5 11. Qf3 Nf6 12. O-O (12. Qb3 $2 Qb6 $1 13. Qh3 Qxd4 14. Nxf7 Qe4+ $1 {and this check is the difference between Qb3? and O-O!}) 12... Qxd4 (12... Nbd7 $4 13. Nxf7 $1 Kxf7 14. Qf5 $1 Nb6 15. Bxe6+ Ke8 16. Qg6#) 13. Qb3 ({And it's a transposition to} 13. Qe2 {.}) *

