antee you, you can get a winning position against 2600+ FIDE GMs with it coz everyone misses White's main idea of this move. They think White's idea is to go Bxe6 !! and then Qg6 . They see that Nbd7 counters this move and immediately play it. But that is not the point of} 10. Qd3 $1 {The whole idea is the f5 -square!!!! O-O? is too slow and does nothing to stop Black's main counterplay with} Nbd7 $1 {Black has almost no problems. That is why it is imperative to stop ... Nbd7 .} 11. Nxf7 $2 Kxf7 12. Qe2 Nd5 13. Qf3+ N7f6 {and Black is a piece up with no problems.}) 10... g5 { This was played in the game between MoAlkhodairy (2048) vs GM. ChessSharkz (2910), 2024. Yes, a GM blundered against the Martian Gambit in a blitz game!!} 11. Bxe6 {Sacrificing the bishop to deflect the bishop from protecting the g6 -square.} Qa5+ (11... Bxe6 12. Qg6+ Bf7 13. Qxf7#) 12. b4 ({Why place the bishop on d2 when you can give just two pawns? :)} 12. Bd2 {was the move played in the game. White was still winning, but as a GM, Black went up, winning the game.}) 12... Qxb4+ 13. c3 {Black is lost. Huge material will drop. } Qb6 14. Bxf7+ Kd8 15. Be6 {Renewing the threat Nf7 +.} Kc7 16. Nf7 Rg8 17. Qg3# {I love chess. I love my gambits.} *

