antee you, you can get a winning position against 2600+ FIDE GMs with it coz everyone misses White's main idea of this move. They think White's idea is to go Bxe6 !! and then Qg6 . They see that Nbd7 counters this move and immediately play it. But that is not the point of} 10. Qd3 $1 {The whole idea is the f5 -square!!!! O-O? is too slow and does nothing to stop Black's main counterplay with} Nbd7 $1 {Black has almost no problems. That is why it is imperative to stop ... Nbd7 .} 11. Nxf7 $2 Kxf7 12. Qe2 Nd5 13. Qf3+ N7f6 {and Black is a piece up with no problems.}) 10... Qc8 { In the ladder, I have not faced this move. It is very difficult to play. But it is good, as it defends the e6 -pawn. This is the most popular move in our daily Martian Gambit arenas.} 11. O-O Nbd7 12. f4 {A very strong move, protecting the pony on e5 , and whenever Black takes on e5 , the f-file will be open.} Nxe5 13. fxe5 Nd5 14. Bb3 g5 15. c4 Nc7 16. Be3 Bg7 17. Qe4 {As you can see, White enjoys space advantage, and they can do whatever they want.} O-O ({After} 17... Qd7 {, the position is very complex with chances for both sides. Black cannot castle short, as they will get mated on the b1 - h7 diagonal.}) 18. Bc2 {And checkmate is unstoppable.} Re8 19. Qh7+ Kf8 20. Rxf7+ {Removing the defender of the king and clearing the f-file for the other rookie.} Kxf7 21. Rf1# {Checkmate. :)} *

