antee you, you can get a winning position against 2600+ FIDE GMs with it coz everyone misses White's main idea of this move. They think White's idea is to go Bxe6 !! and then Qg6 . They see that Nbd7 counters this move and immediately play it. But that is not the point of} 10. Qd3 $1 {The whole idea is the f5 -square!!!! O-O? is too slow and does nothing to stop Black's main counterplay with} Nbd7 $1 {Black has almost no problems. That is why it is imperative to stop ... Nbd7 .} 11. Nxf7 $2 Kxf7 12. Qe2 Nd5 13. Qf3+ N7f6 {and Black is a piece up with no problems.}) 10... Na6 { The idea is to go ... Nc7 to protexct the e6 -pawn and maybe land on d5 . This idea would be great if only White's next move didn't exit. This move has been played by FM SRob2003 (2757) Nov 25, 2024, and IM yosephtaher (3067) Dec 29, 2024.} 11. Bxe6 {Sacrificing the bishop to deflect the f7 -bishop guarding g6 . } Qa5+ (11... Bxe6 12. Qg6+ Bf7 13. Qxf7#) 12. Bd2 {This move is just winning the queen and the game.} (12. b4 $2 {is a very bad move. I messed up the lines; this move is good against} g5 $4 {not against Na6?? , as now the pony can take on b4 . This move was played in CM Witty_Alien (2489) vs. IM Yosephtaher (3067) Dec 29, 2024.}) ({The game followed} 12. b4 $2 Nxb4 13. Bxf7+ Kd8 14. Qd2 Nxc2+ 15. Ke2 Qxd2+ 16. Bxd2 Nxa1 17. Rxa1 Kc7 18. Rc1 g5 19. Ba5+ Kc8 $4 {( b6!⩱ ) } 20. Be6+ $1 Kb8 21. Nxc6+ $3 {Beautiful romantic clearance sacrifice to clear the b-file:} bxc6 22. Rb1# {. Feel free to see the in-game reaction on YouTube – The Gambit that Shocked Mars - Martian Gambit, THE IMPOSSIBLE!! }) 12... Qxd2+ 13. Kxd2 Bxe6 14. Qg6+ {White is winning, as they are a queen up and with more active pieces.} *

