o exchange pieces. Black is a piece up but still has to answer how are they going to develop their kingside. In the meantime, if White castles and plays Rd1 to exchange the rookie on d8 , they will be doing great.} ) 15. a4 {What a beautiful move shown at deep depth by Stockfish. The idea is to go a5 and trap the queen on c5 !! Welcome to the Martian Gambit, a truly out-of-this-world gambit!} ({The game between CM Witty_Alien (2364) vs. CM Schachkatze2000 (2740), Nov 20, 2024, continued:} 15. f4 $5 g5 $2 {It looks like a very good move, as it challenges the center, but opening the f-file favors White.} 16. Be3 Qa5 17. Bxe6 {, still, as you can see, Black just can't develop their kingside. That is the main idea of MG.} Bg7 18. O-O gxf4 19. g5 { , trying to sneak in with the queen on h5 .} fxe3 $4 20. Qh5+ Bg6 21. Qxg6# {.} ) 15... a5 {This looks too natural to be a mistake. It's a mistake, as the queen no longer has the a5 -square when Be3 comes.} 16. f4 {Preparing Be3 , trapping the queen.} Qb6 (16... Rd3 $3 {No, nobody plays this move apart from engines. It's 0.00, of course.}) 17. Be3 Qc7 18. Bxe6 {White is much, much better despite being a full piece down. The bishop on e6 is a monster, and as usual, Black cannot develop their kingside pieces.} *

