on is chaos, but Black is much better, as they are a piece up.}) 13. Bxh7 Rxh7 14. Qd3 Bxe5 (14... Rh8 15. Qg6+ Kf8 16. Qf7# {1-0} ) 15. Qxh7 Bg3+ 16. Ke2 Kd7 17. hxg5 hxg5 18. Bxg5 Na6 19. f4 ({Tadaaa! The bishop, all of a sudden, is trapped! Qb6} 19. Rag1 {Qxb2 Rxg3 Qxc2+ (nice try) Qxc2+- . :)}) *

