h7 13. Qd3 Qd5 (13... g5 $4 14. Qg6+ Rf7 15. Qxf7#) 14. c4 {This move is very strong. In the Bh7 line, White does not have this move, as there Black has ... Qe4 +, exchanging queens.} Qa5+ 15. Bd2 Qb6 16. Qg6+ Kd8 17. O-O-O ({Look at White's position. Pure romance. Black has no way to develop their pieces against the positional bind, whereas White's play is simple: just to open the center. Qxd4 fails to} 17. Ba5 {b6 Rxd4+ .}) *

