 person: DON'T play Bc4 , but play g4! That is what I do.} 10. O-O Nd7 11. Nf3 {A very good move. h5 did not come for free. It left the g5 -square very, very weak.} Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Ngf6 14. Bxe6 {White is almost winning, as Black cannot develop their kingside + the weaknesses on their light squares.} *

