ing a vital pawn.} Qd6 12. Bf7+ Kd8 13. Bb3 {Renewing the threat of Nf7 +.} Bd5 14. c4 ({It's imperative to remember, before taking on e6 , that the pawn is not on b5 . Now this move wins: Bxh1} 14. Nf7+ Kc7 15. Nxd6 {.}) *

