1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng5 Nf6 6. N1f3 Bg6 7. Bc4 h6 8. Ne6 {Hello there! :) How are you? Please make sure you have learned the previous chapters before learning this one. It is imperative to know the Alien and Martian Gambits before this chapter. Here, you will notice how important it is to wait for ... h6 before going for AG and MG. Without Black's ... h6 , you have no compensation for the pony. My Three Lifelines: A. Develop quickly and wait until Black plays ... h6 to transpose to AG or MG. B. Make sure you always make a move that makes you transpose to AG or MG after Black's ... h6 . C. Remember that any transposition suits you as you know the plans, ideas, pattern recognition, etc.} *

