1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 ({Playing the pony on d2 or c3 does not matter much at all. I personally like it on d2 , as if now g6 (Gurgenidze Variation) , Black prepares to fianchetto the bishop on g7 , creating pressure against White's d4 -pawn. Now after} 3. c3 {, the fianchettoed bishop has little to do because of the pawn chain on the dark squares.}) 3... dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 { This is considered the Main Line of the Caro-Kann Defense and the most popular move.  With 4... Nf6 , Black immediately challenges White's central Pony, aiming to provoke exchanges that can help simplify the position and alleviate White's early pressure It's remarkably trendy these days,} 5. Ng5 ({ This move initializes the Alien Gambit! At least in chess.com! For my dear viewers and me, Alien Gambit starts after h6 , and Nxf7!! So, to state that this move is already bringing us to the Alien Gambit is wrong. Here, you can even transpose to the Martian Gambit if Black plays Bf5} 5. Nf3 {Bg6 Bc4} h6 { and Ne6!! Chess.com told me that the decision is based on the following: if you go Ng5 , you plan to sacrifice, but Black is not forced to go ... h6 , even though 90% of the people play ... h6 . The idea of Ng5 is simple. Play for the Alien Gambit! When you play this move, don't ever think of going back with the pony.}) (5. Nxf6+ {is the most common move and the move I used to play a lot before I invented the Alien Gambit. Korchnoi (or Tartakower) Variation, Black's} exf6 {, is regarded as sounder than gxf6!? , the Bronstein-Larsen Variation, which offers Black rapid development, though also ceding White the superior pawn structure and long-term prospects (Black has to be cautious that the d-pawn is now a potential passed pawn in the endgame).}) ( {Since we won't play Nxf6 but hop with the pony on g5 , we stop the lines here. } 5. Ng3 {is a move I played a lot, with bad results after} h5 $1) 5... c5 { I have faced this move only after I have beaten them with the Alien Gambit many times, and they try to avoid it. Black knows the Alien Gambit and they know how OP it is, so they don't want to go into it. So they play ... c5 to attack the center using the weird position of the pony on g5 .} 6. N1f3 { Perfecto move!! We can still transpose to the Alien Gambit. Now Black's only move is ... h6 ; after all others, White is tiny better.} h6 7. Nxf7 {Alien Gambit!!} Kxf7 {Now, it's a pure transposition. Here, d5 and Ne5+ are both amazing moves.} 8. d5 ({Please check} 8. dxc5 {in the Alien Gambit chapter.}) *

