pening is valued for its flexibility and adaptability. This move was played most notably in Game 2, Vishy Anand vs Magnus Carlsen – 2013 World Chess Championship, which gave Magnus an easy draw with Black (because Vishy didn't play Ng5! :-))} 5. Ng5 {After everything has been said for 4...Bf5 , this move comes with shock to people, and if you know what you are doing, you can win VERY easily. When attacking, never go back! Still preparing to sacrifice on f7 after ... h6 . I am sure after this move, Black is out of home prep.} (5. Ng3 {is THE most popular move, but with good play, Black is doing more than OK.}) 5... Bg6 {The most popular move, at least from personal experience. I get this move most often, as there is no Alien Gambit anymore. Also, it's often pre-moved as everyone plays 5.Ng3 attacking the bishop on f5 . Now Black is ready to kick the pony with ... h6 .} 6. N1f3 { Now, according to the engine, the only move for Black is ... h6 , which is perfect as we get the Martian Gambit. Every other move is weak.} e6 {This move is just to tilt us and not allow MG. :(((( It's a weak move that allows Ne5 and Black will be in a terrible position, yet they do play ... e6 coz they are afraid of MG.} 7. Ne5 Nd7 8. Nxg6 hxg6 9. h4 Ngf6 10. Bc4 Bd6 11. Qe2 Qe7 12. Bd2 O-O-O 13. O-O-O {White is much, much better. Super duper strong pony on g5 , bishop pair advantage, and more space. As you can see, if Black doesn't allow AG and MG, we just have a perfecto pony on g5 . :-)} *

