1. e4 d5 2. Nc3 dxe4 3. Nxe4 Bf5 4. Ng5 Bg6 5. N1f3 h6 6. Ne6 {Here, my dear brothers and sisters, I will show you how you can get the Alien and Martian Gambits from other openings. Please note that it's LESS effective, as we are a full tempo down, and this is too much. Still, I have won so many games, as the plans are the same. My goal is to make the Alien and Martian Gambits generic with both colors. Please learn this chapter only after learning the gambits. Good luck, have fun!❤ Why it works even a tempo down is because you use knowledge and pattern recognition. Trust me; I have a mindblowing win rate with those tempi-down gambits because the plans are the same. My Five Lifelines: A. Do not lose heart that you are tempi down. Follow the same plans and ideas as you would use in a normal AG and MG. B. Make sure you follow the exact plan with Bd3 , O-O , and Re1 followed by Ne5 (4)+. C. If your opponent plays aggressive-looking moves early on, then attack as fast as possible, as you probably don't have the time for Bd3 , O-O , and Re1 followed by Ne5 (4)+. D. It's very important that you believe you can win and that the gambit is OP. Otherwise, you will double-question your moves. E. Know that it is less effective than normal AG and MG. I always play them when given the chance; I have beaten GMs with the Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation.} *

