1. e4 e6 {This is the French Defense.} 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Ng5 Bd6 {I want you to show one of the most beautiful openings, which is brilliant if Black avoids the Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation.❤} 6. N1f3 Nbd7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Qe2 {Amazing move, indirectly defending against ... h6 h4 !! and ... e5 !} h6 9. h4 {Brilliant Pony Sacrifice. Black cannot take, as they will get easily mated on the h-file.} hxg5 10. hxg5 ({Now the rookie on h1 is a monster. Black is getting mated: Nd5} 10. Bh7+ Kh8 11. Ne5 Bxe5 12. Qh5 g6 13. Bxg6+ Kg7 14. Qh7+ {.}) *

