1. e4 e6 {This is the French Defense.} 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Ng5 Bd6 {I want you to show one of the most beautiful openings, which is brilliant if Black avoids the Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation.❤} 6. N1f3 Nbd7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Qe2 {Amazing move, indirectly defending against ... h6 h4 !! and ... e5 !} h6 9. h4 {Brilliant Pony Sacrifice. Black cannot take, as they will get easily mated on the h-file.} e5 {A fantastic move that makes use of the white queen and king placement.} 10. Ne6 {Man, I could have played this move so many times, and I always missed it until I analyzed a game I played with GM Vladimir Raicevic on Nov 19, 2024. I almost cried with beauty when I saw the engine top move is Ne6 !! What a mindblowing, beautiful move on move 10!!!!!! As you can see, in the Alien Gambit, the pony on g5 , if not kicked with ... h6 , is a super duper strong piece. This move closes the e-file, and then the fork will come dxe5 , getting the piece back in a better position. Feel free to see game reaction on YouTube – Mindblowing Pony Brilliant ‼️ (yes, I finally got to play it!❤)} (10. dxe5 $2 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. Qxe5 Re8 {and Black wins the queen with an easy winning game.}) 10... fxe6 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13. Qxe5 {White got their piece back, with a better pawn structure. All they have to do is castle, and they will have a much better position. Black needs to do something fast.} Ng4 14. Qe4 Nxf2 15. Qh7+ Kf7 16. O-O {Yes, my dear friend, you can castle when your rookie is under attack. A pattern I found difficult to understand as a kid.❤} Qd4 17. Be3 {Stop it bebe!!! Sacrificing The bishop to deflect the queen from protecting the g7 -pawn.} Qxe3 18. Bg6+ Ke7 19. Qxg7+ Kd6 20. Qxf8+ {Black loses tons of material, and White is easily winning.} *

