1. e4 e6 {This is the French Defense.} 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Ng5 h6 6. Nxf7 {The Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation!! Bonjour because it's against the French. It's super duper popular, and I have won against so many GMs with it. Still, it's less effective as the pawn is not on c6 , and there is already a pawn on e6 , reducing errors from Black. Feel free to learn it on YouTube – The Gambit That Shocked France - Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation .} Kxf7 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Bd3 Bd6 9. O-O Rf8 10. Re1 {No matter what Black responds with in the Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation, we follow up with Bd3 , O-O , and Re1 . Of course, if Black plays ... c5 before ... Nc6 , we need to protect the pawn on d4 with c3 .} Kg8 11. c3 ({It's imperative to protect the d4-pawn before jumping with the pony on e5 . Bd7} 11. Ne5 Bxe5 12. dxe5 Nd5 13. Qg4 {Be8 Qxe6+ Bf7 Qf5} g6 14. Qh3 h5 15. Bh6 $1 ({The game between CM Witty_Alien (2436) vs. GM Pablozarnicki (2641), Sep 21, 2024, continued: e6? Qe7?? exf7+ Qxf7} 15. Qg3 Kh7 16. c4 Ndb4 17. Be4 Nd4 18. Qh4 Kg8 19. Bh6 Re8 20. Rad1 c5 21. a3 Nbc2 22. Bd5 $1 {Rxe1+ Rxe1} Nxe1 23. Qf6 $1 {What a beautiful move. Using the pin. The pin is indeed mightier than the sword.} Qxd5 24. Qg7# { . What a beautiful game. I was the happiest. Feel free to see my reaction on YouTube – Alien Gambit Bonjour Variation Against GM .}) 15... Re8 {e6+– and White is crushing. The bishop is trapped, and the black king is very weak.} ) *

