1. e4 c5 {This is the Sicilian Defense.} 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 e6 4. cxd4 d5 5. Nc3 dxe4 6. Nxe4 Nf6 7. Ng5 h6 8. Nxf7 {The Alien Gambit Siciliano Variation!!} Kxf7 9. Nf3 Nbd7 10. Bd3 Bd6 11. O-O Re8 12. Re1 Kg8 13. Ne5 Bxe5 14. dxe5 Nd5 15. Qg4 Kh8 16. Qh5 (16. Bxh6 $2 gxh6 17. Qg6 Qe7 {, as you can see in this Siciliano Alien Gambit, the c-pawn has been exchanged, so there is no c4 !} 18. Qxh6+ Kg8 19. Re4 Qg7 {and Black defends with two pieces up.} 20. Qh5 {, all seems good, right? Rg4 is coming.} N7f6 $3 {Beautiful move. That is why aggressive chess wins you games, and positional chess wins you championships. One mistake and your opponent can return some material back and win the game. Sacrificing the pony so the other can replace it with a fork while protecting the e8 -rookie:} 21. exf6 Nxf6 {.}) 16... Nc5 17. Bxh6 gxh6 18. Qxh6+ Kg8 19. Bh7+ Kf7 20. Qg6+ Kf8 21. Qg8+ Ke7 22. Qg7# {A very familiar checkmate, right? :)} *

