1. e4 d5 {This is the Scandinavian Defense.} 2. Nc3 dxe4 3. Nxe4 Bf5 4. Ng5 Bg6 5. N1f3 h6 6. Ne6 {The Martian Gambit Viking Variation!! Please play at your own risk. White is a critical tempo down, but do not lose heart. The knowledge learned can still be applied here.} fxe6 7. Ne5 Bf7 8. Bc4 ({The plans are the same. This move is interesting and the one I reccomend, but feel free to learn } 8. Qf3 $1 {too.}) 8... Qd4 {As you well know, this move cannot be played in normal MG because White's pawn is on d4 and Black's pawn is on c6 .} 9. Qe2 { Now e6 should be defended.} Qb6 {The most human move, to protect the e6 -pawn, but now White has the Martian Gambit grip and is much better.} 10. O-O Nf6 11. d4 {The pawn cannot be taken, as Nxf7 comes followed by Qxe6 +.} g5 12. a4 a5 13. Ra3 Bg7 14. Nxf7 Kxf7 15. Re3 {Despite White being a full piece down, they are winning, as Rxe6 will come with deadly checkmate threats. The Martian Gambit Viking Variation is indeed out of this world.} Nd5 16. Bxd5 exd5 17. Rxe7+ Kf8 18. f4 {Black will get checkmated.} g4 19. Re8+ Kf7 20. Qe7+ Kg6 21. f5+ Kh5 22. Qf7+ Kh4 23. g3+ Kh3 24. Qh5# {As you can see, Black never had the time to develop their queenside pieces, mainly because any pony move would have allowed Nxf7 followed by Qxe6 +.} *

