1. e4 d5 {This is the Scandinavian Defense.} 2. Nc3 dxe4 3. Nxe4 Bf5 4. Ng5 h6 ({Wait... Is} 4... h6 {marked as '?' This gotta be a mistake, right?}) 5. Nxf7 {THE ALIEN GAMBIT VIKING VARIATION IS BRILLIANT!!! Shocking right? The fact that the pawns are NOT on c6 and d4 is in White's favor, as we will see.} Kxf7 6. Qf3 {Tada!! Black will lose the bishop, has a weak king, and a worse pawn structure! In a normal Alien Gambit against the Caro-Kann, the black pawn is on c6 and the white pawn on d4 , so here there would be ... Qd5 ! For Black, that would just win the game!} ({e6 or g6 won't save the bishop due to} 6. g4 { .}) 6... Kg6 {The game between CM Witty_Alien (2603) vs. Chepakh (2662), Jan 30, 2025, continued: 6... Qd7 ? Protecting the bishop this way does not work, as g4 will win it back regardless.} ({g4!} 6... Nf6 {gxf5 and White is completely winning. We are a pawn up, and Black's light squares are so weak.}) {Qxf5? This bad move was played during the game, but I managed to win regardless, as White is still much better. Feel free to see my reactions on YouTube – Alien Gambit Viking Variation IS BRILLIANT!!} 7. Qxb7 {Okay, you might think the rookie on a8 is attacked, but after ... Nd7 , Black is just a piece up, no?} (7. g4 $2 Bxc2 $1 8. Qxb7 Nf6 $3 {Brilliant move. It's all about the e4 -square.} 9. Qxa8 Be4 {and Black is winning, as they will win back the rookie, with a piece up.}) 7... Nd7 {Now what?} 8. g4 {In the midst of chaos, White has the audacity of hope to go g4 !! This is the only move not to lose the game and the whole idea of Nxf7!! White is +1 here. Shockingly enough, the bishop is kinda trapped!} Bxc2 {This would be a perfect move if it does not drop the bishop.} 9. Qc6+ e6 10. Qxc2+ {Black's king is too weak, the light squares too, and Black's pawn structure is very bad. White is winning.} *

