1. e4 d5 {This is the Scandinavian Defense.} 2. Nc3 dxe4 3. Nxe4 Nf6 4. Ng5 h6 5. Nxf7 {The Alien Gambit Viking Variation!!⛵ Viking because it's against the Scandinavian Defense.} Kxf7 6. Nf3 e6 (6... Bg4 $4 {is a very, very common blunder. Black is not used to having their king on f7 that early in the game:} 7. Ne5+ {.}) 7. d4 Bd6 {Black is so in a hurry to make an artificial castle that they don't even bother with ... Nbd7 or ... Nc6 .} 8. Bd3 Rf8 9. O-O Kg8 10. Re1 Nc6 11. c3 ({As you can see, the two drawbacks of AG Viking Variation: Black has the c6 -square for the pony, and we cannot jump on e5 right away, as that will blunder our very important d4 -pawn:} 11. Ne5 $4 Nxd4 {.}) 11... Bd7 12. Ne5 Bxe5 {Everyone takes... Do not lose heart; they will take against you too. :))} 13. dxe5 Nd5 14. Qg4 Kh8 15. Qe4 ({The game between CM Witty_Alien (2419) vs. joaosilveira12 (2413), Nov 27, 2024 continued:} 15. Bxh6 $2 gxh6 16. Qg6 Qe7 17. Qxh6+ Kg8 18. Re4 Qg7 19. Rg4 $3 {Alien Gambit Viking Variation!! Sacrificing the rookie to deflect the queen protecting the h7 -square.} Nf4 { ( Qxg4} 20. Qh7+ {) Qxg7# Feel free to see my funny reaction to this game on YouTube – I think he said ALIEN GAMBIT Viking Variation . :))}) 15... Rf5 ( 15... Kg8 $2 16. Qh7+ Kf7 17. Bg6+ Ke7 18. Qxg7+ Rf7 19. Qxf7#) 16. g4 Nce7 17. gxf5 Nxf5 18. Qg4 {White is winning, as they are not only an exchange up, but they are also attacking.} *

