1. e4 d5 {This is the Scandinavian Defense.} 2. Nc3 dxe4 3. Nxe4 Nf6 4. Ng5 h6 5. Nxf7 {The Alien Gambit Viking Variation!!⛵ Viking because it's against the Scandinavian Defense.} Kxf7 6. Nf3 Nc6 {I don't like facing this move. :(( Now, ... Bg4 is a very annoying threat. Luckily, they don't usually play ... Bg4 after d4 but ... e6 , and we can follow our plan.} 7. d4 Bg4 {The drawback of the Alien Gambit Viking Variation is easily seen here. This move is very strong, as the pony on f3 is very important to jump on e5 after Bd3 , O-O , Re1 , and Ne5 +.} 8. c3 {The d4 -pawn needs to be defended, as there are threats of ... Bxf3 followed by ... Nxd4 with an easy win for Black. CM Witty_Alien (2441) vs. FM Gerasimenyuk_Miha (2416) Jan 1, 2025, continued:} Qd7 9. Qb3+ e6 10. Qxb7 Rb8 ({Everybody blunders this. They are not used to seeing the tactic that comes next.} 10... Bxf3 11. gxf3 Rb8 {and Black is winning, as they are a piece up.}) 11. Qxc6 {What a beautiful and so romantic tactic. Sacrificing the queen to remove the defender of the e5 -square and deflect the queen on c6 .} Qxc6 12. Ne5+ Kg8 13. Nxc6 {White is up material with an easy win ahead.} *

