1. d4 e5 {This is the Englund Gambit. I play it all the time, it is a very good gambit. You can flip the board for Black here. :)} 2. c3 Nc6 3. dxe5 Nxe5 4. Nf3 Ng4 5. h3 Nxf2 {Alien Gambit with the black pieces!!! OMG, I LOVE CHESS!!} 6. Kxf2 Nf6 {Smart move. This over ... d5 , so we can set up the most popular blunder − Bg5 , hehehehe.} (6... d5 {is another good move if you know your opponent will play c4 , aka he knows how to counter the gambit. The game between CM Witty_Alien (2465) vs. sakthi09 (2430) , Feb 5, 2025, continued:} 7. c4 {. As you can see, this is an Alien Gambit but with tempi down. :( In a normal AG, the pony is on f6 .} c6 8. Nc3 Nf6 9. e3 Bd6 10. Bd3 O-O 11. Re1 Re8 12. cxd5 cxd5 13. Kg1 Ne4 {. The problem is that this does not come with check, so you gotta bluff they won't take on d5 . Which, most of the time, they don't. That is why you play with your own risk my dear friends. My opponent knows the c4 move to stop the gambit, even when we are a tempi down.} 14. Bxe4 $6 {( Nxd5+– )} dxe4 15. Nd4 $2 Qg5 $1 16. Nf5 $4 Be5 $1 (16... Qxf5 $4 17. Qxd6) 17. Nxe4 Qxf5 18. Nd6 Qg6 $3 {Beautiful rookie sac. The idea is .. . Bxh3 , then take on e8 with the rookie with a winning attack.} 19. Nxe8 Bxh3 20. Nf6+ gxf6 21. Qf3 Bg4 $1 22. Qf2 Rc8 23. e4 Bh3 24. Be3 Bg3 25. Qf3 Rc2 $3 26. Rec1 Bxg2 27. Qxg2 Bh2+ $3 {So romantic. Sacrificing the bishop to clear the queen on g6 for the attack on g2 .} 28. Kf1 Qxg2+ 29. Ke1 Qe2# {. I hope you enjoyed this game my dear reader.}) 7. e3 (7. Bg5 $4 Ne4+) 7... d5 8. Bd3 Bd6 9. Re1 O-O 10. Kg1 Re8 11. Nbd2 Ne4 12. Bxe4 dxe4 13. Nd4 Qg5 14. Nf1 Bxh3 15. Qc2 c5 {As you have seen in the Alien Gambit, this is always a very important move. The pony on d4 is very strong. It needs to be kicked to a less active square.} 16. Nb3 Re6 {With a devastating attack. As you can see, the bishop and rookie on a1 are super duper passive.} *

