1. d4 e5 {This is the Englund Gambit. I play it all the time, it is a very good gambit. You can flip the board for Black here. :)} 2. c3 Nc6 3. dxe5 Nxe5 4. Bf4 Ng4 5. Bg3 N8f6 6. h3 Ne3 {Martian Gambit with the black pieces!! The first time I got it, I was the happiest. Feel free to see my reaction on YouTube – Martian Gambit With the Black Pieces!} 7. fxe3 Ne4 8. Bh2 Be7 { We don't have ... Bd6 here, as the pawn is on d7 . :(( This move is good tho, as it stops Nbd2 .} 9. Nf3 (9. Nd2 $4 Bh4+ 10. g3 Nxg3 11. Ngf3 {( Bxg3 Bxg3# ) } Nxh1+ 12. Nxh4 Qxh4+ 13. Bg3 Qxg3# {.}) 9... d5 10. Nbd2 f5 11. Nxe4 fxe4 12. Nd4 O-O 13. g3 c5 14. Nb3 Be6 15. Bg2 Qc7 16. g4 Bh4+ 17. Kd2 Qb6 {With a crazy position. Black has a very strong center, a safer king, and more active pieces. White is a piece up. Of course, here the engines say 0.00. :D} *

