1. d4 e5 {This is the Englund Gambit. I play it all the time, it is a very good gambit. You can flip the board for Black here. :)} 2. c3 Nc6 3. dxe5 Nxe5 4. Bf4 Ng4 5. Bg3 N8f6 6. h3 Ne3 {Martian Gambit with the black pieces!! The first time I got it, I was the happiest. Feel free to see my reaction on YouTube – Martian Gambit With the Black Pieces!} 7. fxe3 Ne4 8. Bf2 Bc5 { We are just following the plans from the normal Martian Gambit, even tho we are tempi down. In normal MG, the pawn would have been on d5 .} 9. Nf3 (9. Qd5 Qe7 $1 {Now White's queen has to go back to d3 , as ... Nxf2 followed by ... Qxe3 + is the threat.}) 9... Qe7 10. Nd4 {Trying to defend against ... Nxf2 , but now the f2 -bishop is weak.} Qf6 11. Nf3 Qe7 12. Nd4 Qf6 13. Nf3 Qe7 { Since you are a tempo down, it's OK to take the draw, even tho I still play for a win here.} (13... O-O 14. Qd5 ({The game between Playchess_VN (2469) vs. CM Witty_Alien (2334), Nov 6, 2024, continued:} 14. Nbd2 $4 Nxf2 $1 15. Kxf2 Qf4 $1 {The beauty! This even works with tempi down!!} 16. Nc4 (16. g3 $2 Qxe3+ 17. Kg2 Qf2#) 16... Qxc4 17. Nd4 Qd5 18. Nf3 Qf5 19. Qd3 Qf6 20. Ke1 d5 21. Nd4 g6 22. g3 Bd6 23. Rg1 c5 24. Nf3 Bf5 25. Qxd5 Rfd8 {and I end up winning the game, keeping my Martian Gambit win rate 100% with both colors. Of course, in arenas, I have lost, but the element of surprise is not there. Still, I am a regular winner there. :)}) 14... Qb6 $3 15. Qxe4 (15. b4 Bxe3 16. Bxe3 Qxe3 17. Qd3 Qc1+ 18. Qd1 Qxd1+ 19. Kxd1 Nf2+ 20. Kc2 Nxh1 {, Black is ahead in material with a winning game. The pony will escape easily via the g3 -square.}) (15. Qb3 Qh6 16. c4 d5 17. cxd5 Nxf2 18. Kxf2 Re8 19. g4 Rxe3 20. Qc4 Rc3+ { , Black is winning as they win the queen.}) 15... Qxb2 16. Bg3 d5 $1 { Beautiful move! Sacrificing a pawn to develop the queenside fast.} 17. Qxd5 Bxe3 $1 {That's a very nice move. Don't take the rookie right away, but guard the escape square for the king on f2 .} 18. Qb3 Qxa1 19. Nd4 Bxd4 20. cxd4 Bf5 21. Kf2 Bxb1 {with ... Qxa2 to follow with a winning game, as Black is an exchange up.}) *

